Colour . The species has been well illustrated in various Japanese and Taiwanese colour publications (see
Miyake 1983
;
Sakai 1976
;
Wang & Liu 1996
). The chela is bright orange in adult specimens, with the fingers deep-red (
Fig. 5
). The colours of the carapace and chelae are similar to those of
P. plicatum
, although the red on the fingers appear to be somewhat darker in the latter species (
Fig. 2
).
